sc_cat_item_producer.description:
An SSL Certificate can either be self-signed (internal) or signed by a certificate authority (external). A self-signed (internal) certificate is free while an SSL certificate signed by a certificate authority (external) comes at a cost.

SSL is a global standard technology used in making a secure encrypted communication channel between a client and a server. It is used by businesses to reduce the risk of theft and tampering of sensitive information while in transit from a client to a server and vice-versa.

NOTE: Please use AMIS - Digicert Certificate (Automation) to request external certificate signed by Digicert as Certificate Authority.

SLA: 5 Business Days
sc_cat_item_producer.name: Internal SSL Certificate
